<div id="pf62" class="pf w3 h1b" data-page-no="62"><div class="pc pc62 w3 h1b"><div class="t m845 x2a h72 y19c ff5 fs35 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lessons for Second Quarter, 1985 </div><div class="t m473 x35 h21 y9b2 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sabbath School members who have not received a copy of the Adult </div><div class="t m846 x32 h21 y9b3 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lessons for the second quarter of 1985 will be helped by the following </div><div class="t m847 x32 h21 yc99 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">outline in studying the first two lessons. The title of this series is &quot;Christ </div><div class="t m848 x32 h21 yc9a ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Our Hope.&quot; </div><div class="t m849 x1c h72 yc9b ff5 fs35 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">First Lesson: </div><div class="t m77b x30 h21 yc9c ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE FAMILY OF GOD </div><div class="t m3fb x31 h21 y10d ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEMORY TEXT: Gal. 3:28. </div><div class="t m5f7 x31 h21 yc9d ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THIS WEEK&apos;S STUDY: 2 Tim. 1:1, 2; 4: 9-21. </div><div class="t m84a x31 h21 yc9e ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">CENTRAL THOUGHT: Sinners, estranged from God, become mem-</div><div class="t m84b x32 h21 yc9f ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bers of God&apos;s universal family through being adopted in Christ. They </div><div class="t m555 x32 h21 yca0 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">then develop a family relationship with their brothers and sisters in Christ </div><div class="t m63b x32 h21 y611 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that is often closer than natural family ties. </div><div class="t m84c x31 h21 y6d5 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">OUTLINE: </div><div class="t m770 x82 h21 y6d6 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I. </div><div class="t m6ca x40 h21 yca1 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Paul&apos;s Relationship to Timothy (2 Tim. 1:1, 2). </div><div class="t m3c7 x31 h21 yca2 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">II. </div><div class="t m1c4 x40 h21 y6d7 ff3 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Timothy&apos;s Love and Obedience (2 Tim. 4:9-21). </div><div class="t m84d x1